    Performance of the 2021 Race-Free CKD-EPI Creatinine- and Cystatin C-Based Estimated GFR Equations Among Kidney Transplant Recipients. 
Few patients with a GFR <30 mL/min/1.73 m2 and the large majority of patients were White. Among kidney transplant recipients the new 2021 race-free CKD-EPI eGFR equations perform similarly to the prior CKD-EPI equations which included race correction terms. No significant difference in performance was observed between the 2021 CKD-EPICr and 2021 CKD-EPICr/CysC equations in the kidney transplant population.
